FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://localhost:5000

# Library Management API

API for managing library books

# Group Books

## Books Collection [/books]

### List All Books [GET]

Returns a list of all books in the library.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "id": 1,
                "title": "Clean Code",
                "author": "Robert C. Martin",
                "isbn": "978-0132350884",
                "year": 2008,
                "available": true
            }
        ]

### Create a New Book [POST]

Create a new book in the library.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "title": "Clean Code",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "isbn": "978-0132350884",
            "year": 2008,
            "available": true
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 1,
            "title": "Clean Code",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "isbn": "978-0132350884",
            "year": 2008,
            "available": true
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "Invalid input"
        }

## Book Detail [/books/{id}]

### Get Book by ID [GET]

Get details of a specific book.

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (number, required) - The book ID

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 1,
            "title": "Clean Code",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "isbn": "978-0132350884",
            "year": 2008,
            "available": true
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "Book not found"
        }

### Update a Book [PUT]

Update an existing book.

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (number, required) - The book ID

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "title": "Clean Code",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "isbn": "978-0132350884",
            "year": 2008,
            "available": false
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 1,
            "title": "Clean Code",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "isbn": "978-0132350884",
            "year": 2008,
            "available": false
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "Book not found"
        }

### Delete a Book [DELETE]

Delete a book from the library.

+ Parameters
    + id: 1 (number, required) - The book ID

+ Response 204

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "Book not found"
        }
